commit.message:
https-ify sass-lang.com urls

See https://github.com/sass/sass-site/issues/217

Committed via https://github.com/asottile/all-repos

Remove reference to src/functions.hpp

See sass/libsass#2793

Remove reference to src/functions.hpp

See https://github.com/sass/libsass/pull/2793

Port over some Makefile changes from libsass

1. Use `cc` and `c++` for compatibility with systems where gcc is not
   installed or is not the default compiler.
2. Use `c++11` standard instead of c++0x.
3. Flatten nested ifs in UNAME/TARGET detection.

Default precision to 10

This lines up with Ruby Sass and Dart Sass.
Also it makes life easier in Sass Spec

commit.message: Fix a minor typo in sassc.c

Revert "Add --import-extensions flag"

This reverts commit 548744e1d8a68c003c86d0e47ee3078a6a327473.

Create CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md

Copied from Ruby-Sass

Fix optional short source-map argument

> Two colons mean an option takes an optional arg; if there
> is text in the current argv-element (i.e., in the same word
> as the option name itself, for example, "-oarg"), then it
> is returned in optarg, otherwise optarg is set to zero.

Add --import-extensions flag

This will enable consumers to continue using raw css imports when
it's remove from LibSass.
